Event_Description: ARMS are deployed at the outlet of the small bay of Tjärnö Marine Lab at the lower end of the photic zone and close to the drop off into the Koster groove (100 m depth). The habitat is soft sediment mixed with rocky seafloor, covered with dead man?s fingers and brown algae (Fucus).

ARMS are deployed in the Kosterhavet National Park nearby the outlet of the small bay of Tjärnö Marine Lab at the lower end of the photic zone and close to the drop off into the Koster groove (100 m depth). The habitat is soft sediment mixed with rocky seafloor, covered with dead man?s fingers and brown algae (Fucus).
